metadata.description: A nature fantasy tale of two children, who are visiting their grandparents in New Zealand, exploring the magical “Bush” (forrest) with their fairy guide Kowhai. Through encounters with various creatures of The Bush, they learn lessons in coping with childhood stresses, while helping uncover a plan that may put the nature creatures in danger. Original music help share the teachings of some of the mystical creatures they meet along the way like The Fog Weaver and Brother Wind. for ages 4-8.
